cember%201%2C%202023%2C%20by%20the%20Russian%20Defense%20Ministry.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDrones%20have%20been%20present%20in%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20on%20a%20scale%20and%20in%20ways%20not%20previously%20seen%20in%20conflict%20before.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBoth%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20publish%20extensive%20drone%20footage%2C%20sometimes%20first-person%20views%20of%20graphic%20attacks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20videos%20feed%20a%20larger%20information%20war%2C%20as%20both%20sides%20lean%20into%20the%20propaganda.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Ukrainian%20drone%20flying%20high%20above%20a%20snowy%20white%20landscape%20spotted%20a%20group%20of%20Russian%20troops%20walking%20along%20a%20tree%20line%20somewhere%20near%20war-torn%20Avdiivka.%20The%20small%2C%20bomb-laden%20aircraft%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etargeted%20one%20soldier%2C%20dropping%20an%20explosive%20a%20few%20feet%20away%20from%20him.%20The%20other%20Russians%20made%20a%20run%20for%20it%2C%20hoping%20to%20find%20cover%20among%20the%20trees%2C%20but%20there%20was%20no%20escaping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%2C%20the%20video%20surfaced%20online%2C%20where%20anyone%20can%20see%20the%20effects%20of%20the%20fighting.%20The%20horrors%20of%20war%20are%20on%20full%20display%2C%20but%20the%20significance%20may%20at%20times%20be%20more%20elusive%20and%20at%20others%20exaggerated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20it%20goes%20in%20the%20ongoing%20drone%20war%20%E2%80%94%20no%20soldier%20or%20vehicle%20is%20safe%20from%20these%20weapons.%20And%20nearly%20two%20years%20after%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%2C%20the%20world%20is%2C%20more%20often%20than%20not%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewatching%20the%20war%20through%20drone%20footage%20posted%20regularly%20by%20both%20sides.%20The%20videos%20feed%20larger%20narratives%20and%20are%20another%20way%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20can%20influence%20public%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20part%20of%20the%20propaganda%20and%20information%20war%20in%20which%20each%20side%20is%20trying%20to%20diminish%20their%20adversary's%20will%20to%20fight%2C%26quot%3B%20Stacie%20Pettyjohn%2C%20director%20of%20the%20defense%20program%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20footage%20can%2C%20accurate%20or%20not%2C%20paint%20a%20picture%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20and%20as%20Ukraine%20seeks%20to%20impress%20its%20Western%20allies%20and%20partners%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzelenskyy-russian-threat-will-only-get-worse-if-ukraine-falls-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceiving%20military%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20something%20not%20guaranteed%2C%20appearance%20and%20influence%20can%20mean%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrone%20videos%2C%20often%20in%20the%20first-person%20view%2C%20are%20spread%20widely%20across%20both%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20Telegram%20channels.%20They're%20then%20often%20circulated%20among%20open-source%20information%20accounts%20that%20document%20various%20aspects%20of%20the%20war.%20They%20flood%20various%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20like%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20videos%20vary%2C%20but%20they%20all%20show%20drones%20flying%20across%20scarred%20battlefields%2C%20locating%20targets%2C%20and%20attempting%20to%20destroy%20them%20in%20one%20way%20or%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20drones%20drop%20deadly%20payloads%20onto%20their%20enemies%2C%20while%20others%20explode%20on%20impact%2C%20flying%20directly%20into%20tanks%2C%20armored%20vehicles%2C%20and%20trucks%2C%20among%20other%20targets.%20Some%20videos%20show%20drone-on-drone%20warfare%2C%20deadly%20attacks%20on%20operators%2C%20or%2C%20like%20the%20footage%20described%20earlier%2C%20attacks%20on%20individual%20soldiers%20caught%20out%20in%20the%20open.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20footage%20being%20released%20by%20both%20sides%20is%20selective%20and%2C%20inherently%2C%20biased%2C%20%26quot%3Bpicked%20to%20show%20the%20attacks%20that%20are%20successful%20and%20that%20support%20the%20overall%20narrative%20that%20they're%20trying%20to%20put%20out%20there%20to%20the%20public%2C%20whether%20domestic%20or%20international%2C%26quot%3B%20Pettyjohn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWar%20watchers%20are%20not%20necessarily%20seeing%20all%20the%20malfunctions%2C%20malpractices%2C%20and%20mistakes.%20The%20drone%20videos%20that%20appear%20on%20open-source%20information%20channels%20or%20are%20shared%20by%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20are%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20operations%20happening%20on%20a%20daily%20basis.%20War%20experts%20have%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20many%20drone%20attacks%20likely%20end%20in%20failure%20for%20one%20reason%20or%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224490%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20military%20learn%20to%20fly%20drones%20with%20bombs%20attached%20at%20a%20special%20school%20on%20May%2012%2C%202023%20in%20Lviv%20region%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657a21730ec98e92f74f3011%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222995%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20military%20learn%20to%20fly%20drones%20with%20bombs%20attached%20at%20a%20special%20school%20on%20May%2012%2C%202023%2C%20in%20Lviv%20region%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EPaula%20Bronstein%20%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20shaped%20by%20the%20constant%20threat%20of%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicles%20(UAVs)%2C%20as%20troops%20on%20both%20sides%20lean%20into%20their%20lethal%20and%20strategic%20potentials.%20The%20scale%20is%20unlike%20any%20conflict%20before%2C%20partially%20because%20both%20combatants%20are%20relying%20on%20them%20so%20extensively%20%E2%80%94%20and%20also%20due%20to%20the%20variety%20being%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20have%20military-grade%20drones%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Ukrainian-made%20R18%20octocopter%20and%20Russia's%20Iranian-made%20Shaheds%20and%20homemade%20variants%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20heavily%20leaning%20into%20commercial%20drone%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20UAVs%2C%20like%20Chinese%20DJI%20Mavics%2C%20are%20cheap%20and%20easy%20to%20put%20together.%20Some%20are%20higher-quality%20racing%20drones%2C%20while%20others%20are%20the%20kind%20of%20simple%20quadcopters%20used%20by%20filmmakers%2C%20photographers%2C%20and%20amateur%20drone%20operators.%20But%20in%20the%20war%2C%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20troops%20can%20pretty%20easily%20McGuyver%20those%20UAVs%2C%20loading%20them%20with%20bombs%20and%20other%20explosives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20multiple%20drones%20are%20needed%20to%20knock%20out%20a%20tank%20or%20armored%20fighting%20vehicle.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20other%20cases%2C%20though%2C%20one%20drone%20is%20enough.%20Operators%20can%20use%20them%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideos-nothing-is-safe-from-exploding-drones-in-ukraine-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehunt%20down%20targets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20chasing%20troops%20or%20vehicles%20relentlessly.%20It's%20a%20terrifying%20reality%20of%20the%20war%2C%20and%20one%20that's%20been%20well%20documented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20forest%20west%20of%20Kreminna%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20FPV%20loitering%20munition%20from%20the%2067th%20Mechanized%20Brigade%20hunts%20around%20a%20Russian%20position%20for%20roughly%20a%20minute%2C%20eventually%20identifying%20and%20then%20flying%20into%20a%20Russian%20bunker%20before%20detonating.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FMZhGTGB8bD%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FMZhGTGB8bD%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20OSINTtechnical%20(%40Osinttechnical)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FOsinttechnical%2Fstatus%2F1706067809409671547%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%2024%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20FPV%20drones%20and%20loitering%20munitions%20make%20the%20front%20lines%20a%20nightmare%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERussia%20is%20also%20attempting%20to%20overwhelm%20Ukrainian%20air%20defenses%20with%20incessant%20attacks%20involving%20military-grade%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Russia%20was%20using%20its%20cruise%20and%20ballistic%20missiles%20to%20attack%20Ukraine%20cities.%20As%20their%20stockpile%20diminished%2C%20Pettyjohn%20said%2C%20they%20started%20coming%20up%20with%20%26quot%3Bnovel%20approaches%2C%26quot%3B%20eventually%20turning%20to%20one-way%20attack%20drones%20like%20Iranian%20Shahed-136%20drones%20or%20Russian-made%20variants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20types%20of%20UAVs%20have%20swarmed%20Ukrainian%20cities%20regularly%3B%20those%20that%20get%20through%20strike%20both%20civilian%20infrastructure%20and%20military%20targets.%20In%20one%20recent%20attack%20on%20Odesa%2C%20Russia%20sent%2044%20drones.%20Ukraine%20said%20it%20shot%20down%2034%2C%20but%20those%20that%20got%20through%20struck%20energy%20facilities%2C%20leaving%20about%201.5%20million%20Ukrainians%20without%20power%20for%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20used%20drones%20to%20strike%20targets%20behind%20enemy%20lines%20too.%20It%20has%20used%20UAVs%20to%20terrorize%20Russia%2C%20with%20the%20country's%20defense%20ministry%20saying%20a%20recent%20attack%20included%20over%2020%20drones%20operating%20across%20a%20variety%20of%20cities%20and%20territories%20including%20Moscow.%20Ukraine%20has%20struck%20military%20airfields%20with%20drones%2C%20destroying%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-bomber-blown-apart-inside-country-is-latest-protection-failure-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20aircraft%2C%20like%20its%20strategic%20bombers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223715%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20soldier%20studies%20FPV%20drone%20control%20during%20training%20at%20a%20drone%20school%20on%20October%2026%2C%202023%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657cb70350edbc52a864f0ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20soldier%20studies%20FPV%20drone%20control%20during%20training%20at%20a%20drone%20school%20on%20October%2026%2C%202023%2C%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EElena%20Tita%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20to%20the%20way%20Russia%20uses%20them%2C%20drones%20can%20be%20a%20stopgap%2C%20keeping%20Ukraine%20from%20wasting%20precious%20long-range%20weapons%20when%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20drone%20footage%20out%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%2C%20however%2C%20been%20from%20front-line%20FPV%20drones.%20Operators%20who%20fly%20FPV%20drones%20wear%20goggles%20to%20see%20from%20the%20drone's%20perspective.%20Controls%20in%20hand%2C%20it's%20almost%20like%20any%20video%20game%3B%20hand-eye%20coordination%20becomes%20essential%2C%20and%20the%20experience%20is%20both%20visceral%20and%20intimidating.%20It's%20as%20if%20the%20viewer%20is%20both%20operator%20and%20the%20drone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeeing%20combat%20through%20that%20perspective%20can%20skew%20and%20influence%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20successful%20Ukrainian%20FPV%20drone%20videos%20shared%20on%20an%20almost%20daily%20basis%20by%20open-source%20intelligence%20channels%20often%20highlight%20Russian%20incompetence%20and%20Ukrainian%20savvy.%20Russian%20videos%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20demonstrate%20a%20major%20military%20power%20punishing%20a%20weaker%20force%2C%20reinforcing%20the%20narrative%20that%20the%20Ukrainians%20cannot%20hold%20out%20indefinitely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20both%20sides%2C%20drone%20footage%2C%20particularly%20FPV%20videos%2C%20seek%20to%20persuade.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20seeing%20the%20FPV%20drones%20that%20fizzle%20out%20before%20they%20hit%20the%20target%20because%20of%20jamming%2C%26quot%3B%20Pettyjohn%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BOr%20the%20ones%20that%20go%20off%20course%20and%20hit%20a%20tree%20next%20to%20a%20tank%20or%20personnel%20carrier.%26quot%3B%20It's%20all%20part%20of%20an%20information%20pipeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20just%20because%20another%20reconnaissance%20drone%20picks%20up%20video%20footage%20of%20a%20successful%20hit%20or%20major%20explosion%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20target%20has%20been%20destroyed.%20There's%20little%20way%20to%20confirm%20such%20details%2C%20selective%20editing%20can%20make%20getting%20an%20accurate%20picture%20difficult%2C%20and%20the%20videos%20frequently%20end%20before%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20unmanned%20attack%20is%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20though%20that%20there%20isn't%20some%20really%20impressive%20flying%20going%20on%2C%20and%20that%20drone%20operators%20are%20exacting%20an%20asymmetric%20toll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlying%20FPV%20drones%20requires%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20skill%2C%20often%20more%20so%20than%20operating%20other%20types%20of%20UAVs%20or%20loitering%20munitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20performing%20some%20really%20amazing%20maneuvers%2C%26quot%3B%20Pettyjohn%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20attempting%20to%20use%20them%20to%20take%20out%20well%20defended%20and%20more%20expensive%20systems%26quot%3B%20like%20tanks%2C%20flying%20around%20the%20armor%20to%20find%20a%20vulnerable%20point%20where%20the%20payload%20will%20do%20maximum%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20FPV%20pilots%20have%20shown%20themselves%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.