A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-parents-pressure-having-kids-career-focused-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20Conquering%20Moon%2C%20India%20Turns%20Its%20Attention%20To%20Black%20Holes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EHaving%20conquered%20the%20Moon%20this%20year%2C%20India%20will%20begin%202024%20with%20another%20ambitious%20attempt%20to%20understand%20more%20about%20the%20universe%20and%20one%20of%20its%20most%20enduring%20enigmas%20-%20the%20black%20hole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20morning%20of%20January%201%2C%20India%20will%20aim%20to%20become%20only%20the%20second%20country%20in%20the%20world%20to%20launch%20an%20advanced%20astronomy%20observatory%20specifically%20geared%20towards%20studying%20black%20holes%20and%20neutron%20stars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20biggest%20stars%20run%20out%20of%20fuel%20and%20'die'%2C%20they%20collapse%20under%20their%20own%20gravity%20and%20leave%20behind%20black%20holes%20or%20neutron%20stars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EX-Ray%20Vision%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20satellite%2C%20named%20XPoSAT%2C%20or%20the%20X-ray%20Polarimeter%20Satellite%2C%20will%20be%20launched%20by%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO's)%20trusted%20rocket%2C%20the%20Polar%20Satellite%20Launch%20Vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20only%20the%20second%20mission%20of%20its%20sophisticated%20class%20after%20NASA's%202021%20mission%20named%20Imaging%20X-ray%20Polarimetry%20Explorer%20or%20IXPE%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Varun%20Bhalerao%2C%20an%20astrophysicist%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20Bombay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20mission%20will%20try%20to%20decipher%20the%20stellar%20remnants%20or%20corpses%20of%20dead%20stars%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20X-ray%20photons%2C%20and%20especially%20their%20polarisation%2C%20XPoSAT%20will%20help%20study%20the%20radiation%20from%20near%20black%20holes%20and%20neutron%20stars.%20Dr%20Bhalerao%20said%20black%20holes%20are%20objects%20that%20have%20the%20highest%20gravitational%20force%20in%20the%20universe%20and%20neutron%20stars%20have%20the%20highest%20densities%2C%20hence%20the%20mission%20will%20unravel%20the%20mysteries%20of%20the%20ultra-extreme%20environments%20that%20one%20witnesses%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20astrophysicist%20said%20neutron%20stars%20are%20tiny%20objects%2C%20anywhere%20between%2020%20and%2030%20kilometres%20in%20diameter.%20But%20they%20are%20so%20dense%20that%20just%20one%20spoonful%20of%20matter%20from%20a%20neutron%20star%20could%20weigh%20more%20than%20Mount%20Everest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReaching%20For%20The%20Stars%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20India's%20third%20mission%20in%20less%20than%20a%20year%20to%20explore%20the%20universe.%20The%20first%20was%20the%20historic%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%2C%20launched%20on%20July%2014%2C%202023%2C%20and%20it%20was%20followed%20by%20Aditya-L1%2C%20a%20dedicated%20solar%20observatory%2C%20launched%20on%20September%202%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20AR%20Rao%2C%20an%20astronomer%20at%20the%20Tata%20Institute%20of%20Fundamental%20Research%2C%20said%20XPoSAT%20is%20a%20unique%20mission%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BEverything%20in%20X-ray%20polarisation%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20surprise%20as%20everything%20is%20new%20in%20this%20field%20of%20astronomical%20exploration'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20keeping%20with%20ISRO's%20frugal%20approach%2C%20India's%20XPoSat%20satellite%20cost%20about%20Rs%20250%20crores%20(approximately%20%24%2030%20million)%20while%20the%20NASA%20IXPE%20mission%20had%20required%20an%20outlay%20of%20%24%20188%20million.%20The%20NASA%20mission%20has%20a%20nominal%20life%20of%20two%20years%2C%20while%20XPoSAT%20is%20expected%20to%20last%20more%20than%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Biswajit%20Paul%2C%20a%20scientist%20at%20the%20Raman%20Research%20Institute%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20who%20is%20one%20of%20the%20key%20drivers%20of%20the%20XPoSAT%20mission%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20investigate%20the%20structure%20of%20intense%20magnetic%20fields%20in%20cosmic%20objects%20and%20the%20behaviour%20of%20matter%20and%20radiation%20in%20extreme%20gravity.%20This%20will%20be%20achieved%20by%20observing%20some%20bright%20X-ray%20sources%20like%20neutron%20stars%20and%20black%20holes%20in%20the%208-30%20kiloelectron%20volt%20range.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Big%20Impact'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20niggling%20worry%20that%20ISRO%20Chairman%20S%20Somanath%20has%20expressed%20about%20the%20XPoSAT%20mission%20and%20Indian%20scientific%20missions%20in%20general%20is%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20user%20community%20is%20still%20rather%20small%26quot%3B.%20He%20said%20younger%20astronomers%20from%20India%20need%20to%20be%20roped%20in%20for%20these%20expensive%20national%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20Indian%20scientists%20are%2C%20however%2C%20very%20excited%20about%20the%20mission.%20Dr%20Dipankar%20Bhattacharya%2C%20an%20astrophysicist%20at%20the%20Ashoka%20University%20in%20Sonipat%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIndia%20is%20exploring%20the%20universe%20with%20targeted%20back-to-back%20missions%20and%20the%20country%20can%20make%20a%20big%20impact%20in%20unravelling%20the%20many%20mysteries%20of%20the%20universe%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20XPoSAT%20mission%20will%20see%20the%20Polar%20Satellite%20Launch%20Vehicle%20undertake%20its%2060th%20flight.%20Besides%20carrying%20the%20469-kg%20XPoSAT%2C%20the%2044-metre-tall%2C%20260-tonne%20rocket%20will%20also%20lift%20off%20with%2010%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703938380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fjlh4u6e8_black-holes_625x300_19_December_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fafter-conquering-moon-india-turns-its-