scow%20launched%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022.%20Ukrainian%20forces%20fought%20fiercely%20for%20the%20city%20but%20were%20unable%20to%20hold%20onto%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20troops%20who%20fought%20to%20save%20Mariupol%20returned%20home%20permanently%20scarred%20while%20others%20never%20came%20home%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20wanted%20the%20strategic%20port%20city%20along%20the%20Sea%20of%20Azov%2C%20which%20had%20a%20pre-war%20population%20of%20nearly%20450%2C000%20people%2C%20so%20he%20could%20establish%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-mariupols-defenders-are-making-their-stand-against-russia-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eland%20bridge%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20connect%20the%20occupied%20Crimean%20peninsula%20with%20Moscow-held%20territory%20in%20Ukraine's%20eastern%20Donbas%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20battle%20for%20Mariupol%20was%20intense%20and%20bloody.%20Russian%20forces%20encircled%20the%20city%20and%20relentlessly%20bombed%20it.%20Ukrainian%20officials%20say%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzelenskyy-says-mariupol-death-toll-likely-higher-russia-war-ukraine-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etens%20of%20thousands%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20people%20were%20killed%2C%20but%20the%20actual%20death%20toll%20remains%20unknown.%20Investigators%20who%20have%20looked%20into%20reported%20atrocities%20have%20accused%20Moscow%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2022%2F06%2Fukraine-deadly-mariupol-theatre-strike-a-clear-war-crime-by-russian-forces-new-investigation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecommitting%20war%20crimes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20deliberate%20attacks%20on%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ukrainian%20defenders%20made%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-claims-capture-mariupol-azovstal-steel-plant-ukraine-resistance-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elast%20stand%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Mariupol's%20Azovstal%20steel%20plant%2C%20where%20they%20spent%20weeks%20holed%20up%20with%20civilians%20as%20the%20Russians%20tightened%20their%20grip%20on%20the%20city.%20But%20by%20mid-May%2C%20with%20much%20of%20the%20urban%20landscape%20left%20in%20ruins%2C%20Kyiv%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-troops-leave-mariupol-azovstal-plant-apparent-surrender-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esurrendered%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20two%20recent%20interviews%2C%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20separately%20with%20a%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20who%20was%20severely%20wounded%20in%20Mariupol%20and%20spent%20over%20a%20year%20in%20Russian%20captivity%20and%20the%20mother%20of%20two%20Ukrainian%20men%20who%20fought%20in%20the%20city.%20One%20of%20her%20sons%20was%20killed%20there%20while%20the%20other%20was%20captured%20and%20is%20still%20being%20held%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mass%20grave%20in%20Mariupol%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F638a2cb5b4290800185cf54b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMen%20lower%20bodies%20into%20a%20mass%20grave%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Mariupol%20on%20March%209%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EEvgeniy%20Maloletka%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20through%20a%20translator%2C%20the%20soldier%20and%20the%20mother%20described%20intense%20combat%20during%20the%20fight%20for%20Mariupol%20and%20horrific%20conditions%20at%20a%20Russian%20prison%20camp%20where%20a%20deadly%20explosion%20occurred%20last%20year%20that%20killed%20dozens%20of%20Ukrainian%20prisoners%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20tried%2C%20actually%2C%20to%20wipe%20Mariupol%20and%20to%20wipe%20our%20people%20from%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20earth.%20Their%20goal%20was%20to%20break%20our%20will%20%E2%80%94%20to%20break%20our%20resilience%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tetiana%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20mother%20whose%20surname%20has%20been%20intentionally%20withheld.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20they%20did%20everything%20possible%20in%20order%20to%20achieve%20that%20goal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Russians%20didn't%20want%20to%20'give%20me%20back'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOleksandr%20Didur%20was%20serving%20with%20Ukraine's%2036th%20Marine%20Brigade%20near%20Mariupol%20in%20positions%20between%20the%20city%20and%20advancing%20Russian%20forces%20when%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20began.%20As%20part%20of%20an%20air-defense%20unit%2C%20his%20combat%20missions%20involved%20protecting%20infantry%20from%20airborne%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20really%20feel%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Oleksandr%20said%2C%20but%20that%20quickly%20changed.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Russians%20started%20attacking%20the%20civilians%2C%20which%20was%20really%20scary.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthey%20started%20bombarding%20civilian%20places%2C%26quot%3B%20explaining%20that%20it%20was%20like%20%26quot%3Bthe%20sky%20was%20on%20fire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstructions%20eventually%20came%20to%20retreat%20to%20positions%20closer%20to%20Mariupol%3B%20the%20infantrymen%20went%20first%2C%20and%20Oleksandr's%20unit%20followed%20them.%20Everyone%20knew%20the%20war%20had%20started%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20clear%20where%2C%20exactly%2C%20the%20Russian%20troops%20were%20located.%20It%20took%20a%20few%20days%2C%20but%20Oleksandr%20and%20his%20fellow%20soldiers%20eventually%20reached%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOleksandr%20was%20involved%20in%20heavy%20fighting%20in%20Mariupol%2C%20engaging%20in%20air%20defense%20as%20the%20Russians%20approached%20the%20city.%20Ukraine%20put%20up%20a%20fight%2C%20but%20the%20Russians%20managed%20to%20surround%20the%20city.%20As%20for%20Oleksandr%2C%20he%20found%20himself%20holding%20a%20perimeter%20with%20a%20dwindling%20supply%20of%20ammunition%20and%20without%20any%20reinforcements%20coming.%20Holding%20the%20line%20in%20Mariupol%2C%20he%20witnessed%20Moscow's%20forces%20shell%20and%20bomb%20civilian%20structures%2C%20acts%20which%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bshocking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222550%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20from%20April%202022%20shows%20damage%20in%20Mariupol.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6584909c1c5c7b8c9a0b3cd4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20map%20from%20April%202022%20shows%20damage%20in%20Mariupol.%3Cp%3EAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20day%2C%20heavy%20Russian%20armor%20moved%20closer%20to%20his%20position%3B%20Moscow's%20tanks%20would%20move%20with%20caution%20at%20first%2C%20but%20they%20soon%20realized%20that%20the%20Ukrainians%20didn't%20have%20enough%20ammunition%20because%20they%20weren't%20striking%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20we%20had%20was%20just%20rifles%2C%20some%20hand%20grenades%2C%20and%20machine%20guns%2C%26quot%3B%20Oleksandr%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20nothing%20against%20heavy%20weaponry%20like%20tanks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued%2C%20explaining%20that%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20have%20any%20anti-tank%20weapons%20to%20fight%20against%20the%20Russians.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%2C%20amid%20the%20fighting%2C%20tragedy%20struck%20on%20April%206%2C%202022.%20Oleksandr%20didn't%20even%20see%20or%20hear%20the%20enemy%20tank%20fire%20at%20him%2C%20but%20next%20thing%20he%20knew%2C%20a%20shell%20exploded%20against%20the%20wall%20right%20next%20to%20him.%20He%20lost%20consciousness%20and%20when%20he%20woke%20up%20a%20little%20over%20a%20week%20later%2C%20he%20was%20in%20Russian%20captivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tank%20blast%20left%20Oleksandr%20with%20severe%20wounds%20that%20are%20still%20causing%20problems%20today%20because%20they%20never%20really%20healed%20properly.%20Shrapnel%20flew%20into%20his%20body%2C%20entering%20his%20head%2C%20an%20eye%20socket%2C%20a%20leg%2C%20and%20an%20arm.%20His%20other%20arm%20was%20fractured%2C%20and%20he%20lost%20several%20fingers%20on%20one%20of%20his%20hands%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Oleksandr%20standing%20next%20to%20a%20rocket%20near%20Mariupol%20on%20March%203%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65848955a79e5746976c6813%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOleksandr%20standing%20next%20to%20a%20rocket%20near%20Mariupol%20on%20March%203%2C%202022.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Oleksandr%20Didur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOleksandr%20later%20found%20out%20that%20after%20the%20blast%20that%20nearly%20killed%20him%2C%20he%20was%20taken%20to%20a%20bunker%20to%20receive%20urgent%2C%20life-saving%20medical%20attention%2C%20and%20at%20some%20point%20later%2C%20he%20ended%20up%20at%20Azovstal.%20His%20unit%20kept%20fighting%20there%2C%20but%20they%20surrendered%20women%20and%20heavily%20wounded%20people%20to%20the%20Russians%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20keep%20them%20all%20alive.%20Many%20soldiers%20were%20killed%20at%20Azovstal%2C%20and%20those%20who%20survived%20also%20ended%20up%20in%20Russian%20captivity.%20The%20troops%20at%20Azovstal%20became%20beacons%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20resistance%2C%20still%20fighting%20even%20as%20all%20hope%20seemed%20lost%2C%20but%20in%20the%20end%2C%20these%20defenders%20were%20forced%20to%20surrender%20in%20May%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Oleksandr%20eventually%20regained%20consciousness%2C%20he%20couldn't%20see%20anything%2C%20but%20he%20could%20hear%20people%20speaking%20Russian%20and%20Chechen%2C%20the%20language%20spoken%20by%20the%20band%20of%20fighters%20led%20by%20the%20warlord%20Ramzan%20Kadyrov%20that%20had%20joined%20Moscow's%20war%20machine.%20After%20a%20week%2C%20Oleksandr%20was%20taken%20to%20a%20hospital%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine's%20occupied%20Donetsk%20region%2C%20where%20he%20spent%20about%20a%20month%20receiving%20limited%20medical%20assistance%2C%20noticeably%20less%20than%20what%20was%20needed%20given%20the%20severity%20of%20his%20wounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20May%2C%20he%20was%20transferred%20to%20a%20prison%20in%20Olenivka%20that%20held%20Ukrainians.%20Oleksandr%20said%20he%20witnessed%20horrific%20treatment%20by%20the%20Russian%20captors%2C%20who%20beat%2C%20tortured%2C%20and%20interrogated%20detainees.%20Because%20he%20was%20so%20heavily%20injured%2C%20though%2C%20he%20largely%20managed%20to%20avoid%20physical%20abuse%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20could%20actually%20have%20killed%20and%20beaten%20people%20to%20death%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSuch%20cases%20happened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mariupol%20destruction%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F641893465c7c99001991b525%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDamaged%20buildings%20are%20seen%20in%20Mariupol%20on%20March%2016%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EStringer%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20food%20was%20also%20%26quot%3Babysmal%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20portions%20were%20tiny.%20Breakfast%20usually%20consisted%20of%20cereal%2C%20lunch%20featured%20watery%20soup%2C%20and%20dinner%20was%20once%20again%20cereal.%20If%20he%20was%20lucky%2C%20he%20would%20occasionally%20get%20a%20few%20pieces%20of%20fish%20or%20potato.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2029%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F07%2F28%2Fone-year-death-ukrainian-pows-explosion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexplosion%20ripped%20through%20the%20prison%