20job%20quota%20for%20the%20Backward%20Classes%2C%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20to%2065%25%3B%20employing%20over%201.25%20school%20teachers%3B%20and%20according%20%E2%80%98government%20servant%E2%80%99%20status%20to%204%2C40%2C000%20contract%20teachers%20in%20Bihar.%20The%20party%20focused%20on%20the%20achievements%20of%20the%20Nitish%20government%20and%20dropped%20hints%20to%20pit%20the%20%E2%80%98Bihar%20model%E2%80%99%2C%20built%20on%20real%20issues%2C%20as%20part%20of%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20campaign%20against%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Hindutva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParty%20cadres%20are%20in%20a%20jubilant%20mood%20over%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20comeback%20as%20the%20president.%20They%20ruled%20out%20any%20possibility%20of%20factionalism%20surfacing%20in%20the%20party%20with%20Nitish%20at%20the%20helm%2C%20underlining%20that%20he%20is%20an%20acceptable%20leader%20for%20everyone%20in%20the%20party.%20Lallan%20who%20accompanied%20Nitish%20in%20the%20car%20to%20the%20JDU%20office%20ahead%20of%20demitting%20his%20position%20too%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20JDU%20was%20united%2C%20is%20united%2C%20and%20will%20remain%20united.%E2%80%9D%20He%20hit%20out%20at%20the%20media%20for%20%E2%80%9Cplaying%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20building%20a%20false%20narrative%20around%20the%20JDU%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20George%20Fernandes-led%20Samata%20Party%20merged%20into%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20of%20Sharad%20Yadav-led%20faction%20in%202003%20and%20became%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20of%20which%20Sharad%20was%20the%20founding%20president.%20Nitish%20took%20over%20as%20its%20president%20in%202016%20and%20continued%20till%20he%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20Ram%20Chandra%20Prasad%20(RCP)%20Singh%20in%202020.%20Lallan%20Singh%20replaced%20RCP%20who%20was%20axed%20from%20the%20party%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELallan%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20quit%20his%20position%20in%20favour%20of%20Nitish%20can%20also%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20light%20of%20the%20electoral%20reality%20in%20his%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency.%20The%20Munger%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20is%20known%20for%20the%20predominance%20of%20the%20Yadavs%2C%20Kurmis%2C%20Extremely%20Backward%20Classes%20(EBCs)%2C%20and%20minorities.%20The%20baton%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20Nitish%20%E2%80%93%20a%20benefactor%20of%20the%20EBCs%20and%20Mahadalits%20%E2%80%93%20is%20likely%20to%20smoothen%20the%20rough%20edges%20in%20the%20relationship%20of%20various%20caste%20groups%20and%20unite%20them%20behind%20Lallan%2C%20an%20upper%20caste%20Bhumihar%20in%20the%202024%20polls.%20Moreover%2C%20it%20could%20weaken%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20rope%20in%20the%20non-Yadav%20EBCs%20who%20are%20crucial%20for%20the%20Munger%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWild%20speculations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReports%20about%20Lallan%E2%80%99s%20exit%20as%20the%20party%20chief%20ahead%20of%20the%20JDU%E2%80%99s%20meet%20set%20in%20motion%20wild%20speculations%20with%20a%20section%20of%20the%20media%20predicting%20that%20Nitish%20might%20be%20replacing%20Lallan%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfacilitate%E2%80%9D%20his%20%E2%80%9Cre-entry%E2%80%9D%20into%20the%20NDA.%20Several%20channels%20said%20that%20Lallan%20had%20got%20%E2%80%9Cclose%20to%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20president%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20discomfiture%20of%20Nitish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20rung%20of%20BJP%20leaders%20asserted%20that%20Nitish%20was%20%E2%80%9Cpeeved%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20not%20making%20him%20convenor%20and%20he%20was%20looking%20for%20%E2%80%9Cways%E2%80%9D%20to%20rejoin%20the%20NDA.%20To%20the%20chagrin%20of%20the%20JDU%20leadership%2C%20such%20rumours%20have%20been%20doing%20the%20rounds%20for%20over%20a%20week%20despite%20all%20the%20top%20party%20leaders%20%E2%80%93%20Nitish%20Kumar%2C%20K.%20C.%20Tyagi%2C%20Lallan%20Singh%2C%20and%20Vijay%20Kumar%20Choudhary%20%E2%80%93%20repeatedly%20denying%20these%20rumours%20and%20demonstrating%20the%20JDU%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cunwavering%E2%80%9D%20commitment%20to%20strengthening%20the%20INDIA%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20against%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%2C%20who%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20uniting%20various%20non-BJP%20leaders%2C%20including%20Samajwadi%20Party%20chief%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%2C%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Delhi%20chief%20ministers%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Arvin%20Kejriwal%20respectively%2C%20under%20the%20umbrella%20of%20INDIA%2C%20clarified%20on%20December%2025%20that%20he%20does%20not%20have%20any%20personal%20ambition%20and%20only%20wanted%20all%20the%20parties%20to%20put%20up%20a%20united%20fight%20against%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20been%20saying%20from%20the%20very%20beginning%20that%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20any%20post%20for%20myself.%20What%20I%20want%20is%20the%20unity%20of%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20and%20sharing%20of%20seats%20among%20them%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nitish%20said%20after%20paying%20tribute%20to%20former%20prime%20minister%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20on%20his%20birth%20anniversary%20on%20December%2025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20a%20section%20of%20channels%20reported%20the%20%E2%80%9Cstories%E2%80%9D%20of%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cannoyance%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20INDIA%20parties%20for%20not%20making%20him%20a%20convenor%3B%20he%20was%20feeling%20%E2%80%9Cinsulted%E2%80%9D%20and%20was%20looking%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cway%20out%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30165410%2FGCiCMDnaoAAy1y2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30165410%2FGCiCMDnaoAAy1y2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%